# Negative test: pre-flight check rejects a call with missing required inputs.
#
# Per OQ #23 (resolved 2026-05-12), the macro engine pre-flight-validates
# `input_vars` against the macro's declared input contract BEFORE any
# statement executes. If one or more required inputs are missing, the
# engine fails with the canonical `invalid_input` envelope listing ALL
# missing keys at once — not just the first.
#
# How to see the rejection:
#   Run with no inputs (every required key missing):
#     npm run script -- examples/17-input-var-missing.fqm
#
#   Run with partial inputs (one required key missing):
#     npm run script -- examples/17-input-var-missing.fqm \
#       --input-vars '{"topic":"AI"}'
#
#   Run with all inputs supplied (success path):
#     npm run script -- examples/17-input-var-missing.fqm \
#       --input-vars '{"topic":"AI","output_path":"Notes/ai.md"}'
#
# Demonstrates:
#   - Required `input_var` declarations (the contract)
#   - Optional `input_var` with a `--default` (does NOT count toward
#     missing-input failures, even if absent)
#   - The pre-flight envelope shape: required_inputs, optional_inputs,
#     provided_inputs, missing_inputs
#   - The macro body NEVER RUNS when pre-flight fails — there are no
#     side effects from a half-executed macro.

# --- Required inputs (both must be supplied) ---
topic = input_var "topic"
output_path = input_var "output_path"

# --- Optional input (does not affect pre-flight result) ---
notes_prefix = input_var "notes_prefix" --default "Auto-generated notes about"

# --- Body (only runs if pre-flight passed) ---

echo "topic: $topic"
echo "output_path: $output_path"

saved = fq.write_document({
  mode: "create",
  path: $output_path,
  title: $topic,
  content: "$notes_prefix $topic"
})

exit {
  summary: "saved notes for '$topic'",
  file: $saved
}
